But i also see the other side<br>
<br>
General EQ day<br>
<br>
get a group standard makeup, warrior monk cleric drui/sammy caster of some kind whatever, lets just look at the warrior/monk<br>
<br>
i lvl 37 he lvl 34<br>
i have 770 ac not sure what his is<br>
i level maxxed on dual wield double attack and 1hs wielding JboM and Centi Longsword taunt also maxxed<br>
<br>
he has 2 KD's<br>
<br>
Not only does he out damage me that i can handle, lose taunt, hey just keep reminding him to fd(which he wouldnt do) so i get it back, but i get damaged worse than him in the long run as well<br>
<br>
to sum up, with max skills available to my warrior at the time  a monk 3 levels lower than me could out hit taunt and had higher defensive abilities than myself. IE - he replaces my role as a tank<br>
<br>
Now after patch, group with the same monk, and he is bitchin about his nerf, see it from my side, sorry but i will tell you all what i told him, change the way u play and move on.<br>
<br>
Monks were never meant to be tanks, and that is what they were before this patch. this puts the roleplaying aspect of the game back on par. I do agree they overdid it, but it needed to happen.<br>
<br>
You all think u have been hard done by, think about all the mid level warriors that kept gettin passed up because monks could outtank us at lower levels<br>
<br>
just my 2cp<br>
<br>
Dont just look at it from your side, look at it from the non twink/average equip warrior that is trying to do his job and failing caus the monks were way overpowered<br>
<br>
Bruenoar Battlehammer<br>
37 warrior<br>
