<br>
But then more things happened. I'm sure some of you remember how Verant player wiped Test. I was pretty horrified by that, and it was somewhat more personal to me as I sometimes played on Test. Then came other brilliant things, such as the Mystere banning incident. If I didn't have some friends who played EQ, I would have quit over that. <br>
<br>
As time went on, I found I was enjoying playing less. And I realised that there were no more goals I had that I could attain, given my playstyle, social habits, and decidedly casual/roleplaying guild. The raids I was invited on were entertaining enough, but I watched as people left behind all of their principles when it came time to dole out the loot. And it got worse as EQ became more and more item centric.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure exactly what it was, but I stopped playing. And then I finally cancelled my account this summer. I didn't enjoy playing Everquest anymore, my friends weren't playing it as much, and my online acquaintances had sort of drifted away. Then there was my belief that Verant didn't care about its customers, and didn't even know how to design a game to be rewarding. I decided, last month, to renew again, just to give it another shot. And then I read the rather large nerf announcement. I barely even had to think about cancelling again. <p><center><img src="http://www3.sympatico.ca/pratte1/RaotSigpic.jpg">
